    Please make sure to copy $PROJECT_DIRECOTRY/res/sound/* to
    $RUN_DIRECTORY/sound/* after building.


2) ANNOTATED RUBRIC. ___________________________________________________________

COMPLETE/INCOMPLETE

Retries used: NONE (2 extra retries left)

[ ] 5 playtest signatures

Game Requirements
========================================
[ ] Level scripting
    [ ] Levels are loaded from external files

        Please see res/level/level.cogs for an example of a level file.

    [ ] Level files follow a specific format
        [ ] Times & spawns

        Please see SCRIPTING, which is the specification for script files'
        formats.

    [ ] Robust parser

        Please see src/game/scriptparser.*. All errors are reported to standard
        error.

[ ] Player has health and can lose
[ ] Feedback
    [ ] Upon health lost
    [ ] Upon successful defense
[ ] Improved defense mechanic

    Press W, A, or D when a bullet overlaps the corresponding defense area in
    the defense ring.

[ ] Game experience
    [ ] Intro screen that requires player input to advance
    [ ] Game screen
    [ ] Game consists of at least one level loaded from file
    [ ] End screen that displays the result and final score

Global requirements
========================================
[ ] Top-level handin directory contains a Qt project file, a README, and an
    INSTRUCTIONS file
[ ] README has a copy of the rubric with explanations of how to verify
    requirements
[ ] README documents any known bugs
[ ] README indicates number of hours taken
[ ] INSTRUCTIONS contains all information needed to play the game
[ ] Engine and game code logically separated
[ ] Engine code well designed
[ ] Game code well designed
[ ] Runs on department machines
[ ] Does not crash
[ ] Works at 800x600 and fullscreen resolutions
[ ] Runs at 30+ UPS and never dips below 20 UPS unless indicated in the specific
    handout


